Really surprising and fabulous meal.  Started with cous cous which was simple and fresh and enjoyable.  Then moved onto the sea egg which is a slow cooked egg with squid ink and seaweed - interesting flavours definitely but probably the only thing I would not order again.  Also had the chicken quesadilla which was nice.  The octopus and potato with smoke was outstanding and it was all we could do to not immediately order another one!  Finished off with the duck cannelloni which was beautiful.
